    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i'm just worried about how much the clinic is gonna charge me right now. i read online that medical grade honey is actually used in hospitals for wound healing because it kills bacteria and keeps the wound moist. if the cut isnt super wide, wouldnt that just work as a natural way to seal it and prevent infection? i really want to avoid the trip if i can just treat it at home.",
